problems.text:
Find all integer solutions to

\begin{align*}
x^2+2y^2+3z^2&=36,\\
3x^2+2y^2+z^2&=84,\\
xy+xz+yz&=-7.
\end{align*}

Find the value of $a$ satisfying

\begin{align*}
a+b&=3\\
b+c&=11\\
c+a&=61
\end{align*}

Let $x$ and $y$ be integers between $0$ and $5$, inclusive. For the system of modular congruences $$ \begin{cases}
x + 3y \equiv 1 \,\,(mod \, 2) \\  
4x + 5y \equiv 2 \,\,(mod \, 3) \end{cases}$$, find the sum of all distinct possible values of $x + y$

problems.solution:
\begin{align*}
a^2+b^2=c^2 &\implies (a+b)^2-2ab=c^2 \\
&\implies (a+b)^2-2\cdot8=12^2\\
&\implies a+b=4\sqrt{10}\\
&\implies a+b+c=\boxed{12+4\sqrt{10}}.
\end{align*}
